SMALL BUSINESS LOANS REGULATIONS, 1993 providing for the administration
of Small Business Loans made after March 31, 1993, for the changes to the
administrative requirements and to the interest rate chargeable by the
lenders, and a limitation on the amount of personal security to be taken by
the lenders to 25% of the amount of the loan.
